text.tspan: As practised in the Puritan tradition.

flowRoot.flowPara: Shell scripts are very handy to automate tasks on the command line. In this workshop we will present shell scripting not as a general-purpose programming language, but one that is best understood and used as a means of assembling and composing executables. By Erick Matsen.
Office hour: 2:30pm Wednesday March 22 in M1-A303
